This option is used to set whether to raise the "SERVICE_EXCEPTION" event when an exception occurs in transaction execution.

The default value of this option is "true", when an exception occurs in a transaction, then the "SERVICE_EXCEPTION" event will be raised.

    To receive the event as a notification, you need to set the notification in "Administration -> Event Rules"

If this option is set ton "false", then the "toString()" message of the exception will be added to the transaction profile.


---

* Default : true
* Type : Boolean 
* Restart : Not Required
* Supported : 5.4.0.2